TopicTitle: [1.3.1] Pood's OPM-VO (Outer Planets Mod - Visual Overhaul) [v0.3.5] [2017-09-23]

Articles.Content: i tried running this in 1.12.5 and things broke left click was not working and i fell dis apointed as opm-vo is a dependency for the outer planets mod volumetric clouds config do youplan to update this mod in the future?

Short answer, no.

Long answer, this mod is just a bunch of configs and textures. If you feel that this mod has stopped functionality in your install, the only thing it could be is the bundled MiniAVC.dll file that was was widely distributed back in the times of KSP 1.3. Either, delete the file from your install (GameData/PoodsOPMVO/MiniAVC.dll) or download and install the mod Zero MiniAVC and give that a try.

You're using a mod that is listed as compatible/to be used with KSP 1.3.1 in an install of KSP 1.12.5. It might be a dependency of the mod Outer Planets Mod Volumetric Clouds but this is more so an issue for the creator of that mod to highlight any issues with installing this mod in an instance of KSP 1.12.5.

Edited February 24 by Poodmund

@OneSaltyPringle I'm getting a MM error when using your POODSOPMVO-Patch.cfg but if I change it to what Poodmund wrote for the config the error goes away.  Error reads: more than one pass specifier detected, ignoring all but the first: OPMVolumetricClouds/Patches/PoodsOPMVO-Patch/@EVE_CLOUDS:BEFORE[OPMVolumetricClouds]:AFTER[PoodsOPMVO]

Having the same warnings in my MM logs.

"[WRN 13:51:19.824] 1 warning related to GameData/OPMVolumetricClouds/Patches/PoodsOPMVO-Patch.cfg"

Not sure if this should be ignored, but I am certainly curious as to what is causing it.

I'm guessing it's related more to OneSaltyPringle's Outer Planets Mod - Volumetric Clouds mod? I am using the Blackrack's EVE-Redux too.

It is, that MM patch in OneSaltyPringle's mod is invalid. You cannot have a BEFORE and an AFTER declaration in a patch.
